Quick update from the [Hotel Grand
Derya](https://www.flickr.com/photos/hendry/6021067536) in [Dogbiscuit,
Turkey](https://twitter.com/#!/kaihendry/status/100221396923322368).

We've done over 4k miles now! We covered some distance from Istanbul, Cappadocia, all
the way here to this Iranian border town.

<a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/jamiekitson/6018436619/" title="Ballooning @ Cappadocia by Jamie Kitson, on Flickr"><img src="https://farm7.static.flickr.com/6023/6018436619_de6f6988c2_z.jpg" width="640" height="424" alt="Ballooning @ Cappadocia"></a>

Cappadocia, although a tourist trap, was actually pretty good. Through the power
of my [twitter
network](https://twitter.com/#!/TurkeyTourismUK/status/99108049226186755), we
probably had the best hotel in Cappadocia at a good price. It had a pool, the
host Hassan arranged a balloon flight the next morning. Fantastic stuff.

