<a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/jamiekitson/6018997382/" title="Kaymaklı Underground City by Jamie Kitson, on Flickr"><img src="https://farm7.static.flickr.com/6008/6018997382_937b50116d_t.jpg" width="66" height="100" alt="Kaymaklı Underground City" align="left"></a><a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/jamiekitson/6018998542/" title="Cappadocia by Jamie Kitson, on Flickr"><img src="https://farm7.static.flickr.com/6020/6018998542_8684e9ddec_t.jpg" width="66" height="100" alt="Cappadocia" align="right"></a>Next after checking cave after cave (btw, I hate caves now) [they were not caves, but hollowed out rock. First the massive [underground city](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kaymakl%C4%B1_Underground_City) and then the [Göreme Open Air Museum](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Churches_of_G%C3%B6reme,_Turkey) - Jamie], we drove till dusk
and "wild camped" in a nice spot. The Turkish countryside has been stunning.


Today we are quickly going to check out [Ishak Pasha
Palace](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ishak_Pasha_Palace) and then try the
Iranian border. Hopefully we'll be over by lunch and then get a 4-5hr drive to
Tabriz to check out another [UNESCO site](https://whc.unesco.org/en/list/1346)
on the way to Tehran.

